    &lt;Title&gt;Excellent Treatment&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Norma Hughes&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;I was referred to the on call ENT doctor as an emergency by my GP. I had a swelling on my neck which turned out to be a deep abscess and so very painful. I was referred on the Wednesday when I was told that I would need an operation to remove it. I was admitted that day, had a CT scan on Thursday and the operation on the Friday. I was treated by a particular consultant and his team who were fantastic. I was informed of each step as it was going to happen, I had a thorough explanation on the morning of my op by the anaesthetist about every stage from start to finish. From the ward staff to the ENT team I received excellent treatment. Seriously, I could not have received better care if I was a private patient. My follow up appointments were the same excellent treatment. I cannot praise the consultant, his team and the hospital enough. Thank you&lt;/CommentText&gt;
